Hello, my code team has been working on vision for the first time over the past couple of days and have run into annoying issues:

  1. PhotonVision says that PhotonPoseEstimator doesnt recognize tag 19
  2. PhotonVision recognizes other tags, but doesnt update odometry with the tags info.
  3. PhotonVision recognizes certain tags, and updates odometry with them, but to incorrect positions.

All the above usually would point to incorrect PhotonVision versions, however, the library is up to date, and the coprocessor is up to date as well (I even checked the internal tag pose list, it is up to date with 2025 information).

It is probably worth mentioning that I was using a coprocessor with an incorrect version, and swapped it out for an updated one.

Github: GitHub - Geneva-Robovikes/Robot2025

Any help would be appreciated!

I would recommend that you start by simulating the vision world.
There’s a great guide for that if you read the docs on simulation. This can help you understand if your problem is a camera issue or if the program itself is faulty.

If you have simulated the vision code, you can open the April Tag Debug Field from Phoenix tuner on glass’s dashboard. This lets you see the April tags that are set on the field.
The debug field is also really helpful, because it lets you see what tags are currently “seen” by the simulated cameras (assuming you’re also simulating your robot’s position). Afterwards, you can check to see if the problems you’re encountering are on the coprocessor, or in your code.

Also, when you say that it’s “doesn’t recognize tag 19”, what do you mean? As in, the tag isn’t detected? Or are you saying that the PhotonPoseEstimator is throwing an error when it sees that tag?
